=Delete Host Address=
This operation is used to delete a Host Address.

==Request==
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Method || DELETE
|-
|Request URI || 
* XML format
 /vtns/{vtn_name}/vbridges/{vbr_name}/ipaddress.xml
* JSON format
 /vtns/{vtn_name}/vbridges/{vbr_name}/ipaddress.json
|}

;Description of request URI elements
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Element || Description ||Required
|-
|vtn_name ||VTN name.
Valid value: Up to 31
characters that can include
alphabets, numbers, and
underscore (except at the
beginning).
||Yes
|-
|vbr_name ||vBridge name.
Valid value: Up to 31
characters that can include
alphabets, numbers, and
underscore (except at the
beginning).
||Yes
|}

;Request body
:None

==Response==
;Response Body
:None

=Set Host Address=
This operation is used to set a Host Address.


==Request==
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Method || PUT
|-
|Request URI || 
* XML format
 /vtns/{vtn_name}/vbridges/{vbr_name}/ipaddress.xml
* JSON format
 /vtns/{vtn_name}/vbridges/{vbr_name}/ipaddress.json
|-
|Request Body(XML format) ||
 <ipaddress ipaddr="{ipaddr}"
  prefix="{prefix}"/>
|-
|Request Body(JSON format) || 
  {
   "ipaddress": {
        "ipaddr": "{ipaddr}",
        "prefix": "{prefix}"
     }
   }
|}


;Description of request URI elements
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Element || Description ||Required
|-
|vtn_name ||VTN name.
Valid value: Up to 31
characters that can include
alphabets, numbers, and
underscore (except at the
beginning).
||Yes
|-
|vbr_name ||vBridge name.
Valid value: Up to 31
characters that can include
alphabets, numbers, and
underscore (except at the
beginning).
||Yes
|}

;Description of request elements
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Element || Description || Required
|-
|ipaddr ||IP address.
Valid value: IPv4 dotseparated
format.
Valid range: 0 - 255
Example: 192.168.1.1
Note: The value of this
parameter must be unique
within VTN.
||Yes
|-
|prefix ||Prefix length.
Valid value: A positive
integer between 1 and 30.
||Yes
|}

==Response==
;Response Body
:None

